.Dd May 28, 2026
.Dt XTC_REG 3
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm xtc_reg_create ,
.Nm xtc_reg_destroy ,
.Nm xtc_reg_register ,
.Nm xtc_reg_unregister ,
.Nm xtc_reg_lookup
.Nd named process registry
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.In xtc.h
.In xtc_reg.h
.Ft int
.Fn xtc_reg_create "xtc_reg_t **out"
.Ft void
.Fn xtc_reg_destroy "xtc_reg_t *r"
.Ft int
.Fn xtc_reg_register "xtc_reg_t *r" "const char *name" "xtc_pid_t pid"
.Ft int
.Fn xtc_reg_unregister "xtc_reg_t *r" "const char *name"
.Ft int
.Fn xtc_reg_lookup "xtc_reg_t *r" "const char *name" "xtc_pid_t *out"
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm xtc_reg
is a name-to-pid registry.  Modeled on Erlang's
.Sq register/2
process registration.  Lets a process find a peer by canonical
name without sharing pid pointers ahead of time.
.Pp
Names are short strings
.Pq up to 64 bytes ;
re-registering the same name with a different pid replaces the
prior binding atomically.
.Pp
xtc_app owns a registry per app
.Pq Xr xtc_app_registry 3 .
Multiple registries are permitted for sharded namespaces.
.Sh EXAMPLES
.Bd -literal -offset indent
xtc_reg_t *r = xtc_app_registry(app);
xtc_pid_t pid;

/* Bind a name to my process. */
xtc_reg_register(r, "metrics_proc", xtc_self());

/* From elsewhere: */
if (xtc_reg_lookup(r, "metrics_proc", &pid) == XTC_OK)
    xtc_send(pid, msg, sz);
.Ed
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr xtc_app 3 ,
.Xr xtc_proc 3 ,
.Xr xtc 7
.Sh HISTORY
Appeared in xtc 0.1.
